  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The aim ordained in the divine purpose, why the Jews, in consequence of having lost the right of life and death, were obliged to answer “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἡμῖν οὐκ ἔξεστιν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".” Otherwise, Jesus, as a false prophet and blasphemer of God, would have been ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "stoned",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (like Stephen, and comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 8:59",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), but would not have been visited with the Roman punishment of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "crucifixion",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", namely, as one guilty of high treason, as He, with His pretensions as Messiah, could not but appear to be before the Roman courts; and the word of Jesus, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 12:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", would have remained unfulfilled.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This, however, they decline to do, because it is the death penalty they desire, and this they have no right to inflict: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἡμῖν οὐκ ἔξεστιν ἀποκτεῖναι οὐδένα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In the Roman provinces the power of life and death, the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "jus gladii",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", was reserved to the governor. See Arnold’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Roman Prov. Administration",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", pp. 55, 57; and Josephus, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Bell. Jud.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ii. 8, 1, who states that when the territory of Archelaus passed to the provincial governor, Coponius, the power of inflicting capital punishment was given to him, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μέχρι τοῦ κτείνειν λαβὼν παρὰ τοῦ Καίσαρος ἐξουσίαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". See also Stapfer’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Palestine",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", p. 100. By being thus handed over to the Roman magistrate it came about that Jesus was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "crucified",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a form of capital punishment which the Jews never inflicted even when they had power; and thus the word of Jesus was fulfilled which He spake intimating that He would die by crucifixion, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 12:32-33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
